{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":70249,"duration_api_ms":67087,"num_turns":16,"result":"Here's what was done and how it all fits together:\n\n## Summary\n\n**`DeviceTypeChangedHandler`** (already existed at line 37) handles the actual type-change logic:\n1. Acquires process lock\n2. Re-reads entity from DB to avoid stale-cache races\n3. Rebuilds fingerprint for the new type\n4. Updates entity: type, fingerprint, resets processing stage to `PENDING`\n5. For `USER_HOST_BINDING`, populates `userId`/`userIdentity`\n6. Updates cache\n7. Re-runs the state machine from `PENDING`\n\n**`CachedExistingEntityHandler`** (the wiring point) — I added:\n- **Line 30**: Injected `DeviceTypeChangedHandler` via constructor\n- **Lines 53-60**: After the version/staleness check but **before** fingerprint comparison, checks if `entity.type != req.entityType`. If they differ, delegates directly to `DeviceTypeChangedHandler`, bypassing the fingerprint logic entirely (since a type change always requires reprocessing regardless of attribute changes).\n\n**Flow**: `Orchestrator` → cache hit → `CachedExistingEntityHandler.handle()` → version check → **type-change check (new)** → fingerprint comparison → `FingerprintHandler`\n\nThe type check is placed after the version check so stale requests are still discarded, but before fingerprint comparison so type changes short-circuit the normal same/different-attributes flow.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7ecb4941-efae-49e9-bdfd-29818a0ee600","total_cost_usd":0.44171749999999993,"usage":{"input_tokens":1717,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30148,"cache_read_input_tokens":321165,"output_tokens":3365,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30148,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":1717,"outputTokens":3365,"cacheRead